TI  == in vitro activity of moxalactam against anaerobic bacteria.
AB  == moxalactam was tested against 80 isolates of anaerobic bacteria from clinical specimens. the results of this study and a review of other studies, in which comparable susceptibility testing methods were used, demonstrated the susceptibility to moxalactam of members of the bacteroides fragilis group, bacteroides melaninogenicus, fusobacterium species, anaerobic gram-positive cocci, and clostridium perfringens.
