PMID== 6259592
TI  == [in vitro activity of cefotaxime on anaerobes (author's transl)].
AB  == the comparative activity of cefotaxime, cefazolin, cefamandole and cefoxitin was  studied on 80 strains of anaerobic bacterial species: 14 clostridia, 60 bacteroides fragilis, 6 peptococcus. the new cephalosporins showed an increase in the in vitro activity against bacteroides fragilis, but their efficacy was still  inferior to that of the 5-nitro-imidazole derivatives.
