PMID== 6264591
TI  == head-space gas chromatography as a tool in the identification of anaerobic bacteria and diagnosis of anaerobic infections.
AB  == the identification of anaerobic bacteria to the species level can be a laborious  and time consuming procedure. gas chromatography offers a diagnostic aid, and the advantages of the recently introduced head-space gas chromatography technique are: it is rapid, accurate and easy to perform; it provides more information of differential diagnostic value; and the identification process can be automated by connecting the head-space gas chromatograph to an automatic injection unit and a  computer which interprets the chromatograms. the head-space technique may be used for direct analyses of clinical specimens for rapid diagnoses of anaerobic infections.
TIHT== 
