PMID== 222015
TI  == concomitant t- and tk-activation associated with acquired-b antigens.
AB  == three patients with acquired-b antigens are reported whose red blood cells also manifested t- and tk-activation. the results of tests using purified arachis hypogaea and bandeiraea simplicifolia (bs ii) lectins, and red blood cells either t, tk or both t and tk-activated by bacterial enzymes in vitro, suggest that the  acquired-b phenomenon, t-activation and tk-activation result from the action of different bacterial enzymes.
